tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE tracking_data (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    user_id INT,
    event_name VARCHAR,
    event_data JSON
)

CREATE TABLE historical_tracking_data (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    date DATE,
    event_name VARCHAR(255),
    user_id INT,
    location VARCHAR(255)
);

CREATE TABLE reporting_data (
    report_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    report_date DATE,
    report_type VARCHAR(255),
    user_id INT,
    report_content TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE historical_tracking_data (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP,
  event_name VARCHAR(255),
  user_id INT,
  data JSON
)

CREATE TABLE user_tracking (
  user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  browser VARCHAR(255),
  os VARCHAR(255),
  last_login TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE event_types (
  event_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  event_name VARCHAR(255),
  description TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE analysis_results (
  result_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  analysis_date DATE,
  analysis_type VARCHAR(255),
  result_data JSON
)
CREATE TABLE historical_events (event_id INT PRIMARY KEY, event_name VARCHAR(255), event_date DATE, event_description TEXT)
CREATE TABLE users (user_id INT PRIMARY KEY, username VARCHAR(255), email VARCHAR(255), join_date DATE)
CREATE TABLE locations (location_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location_name VARCHAR(255), latitude DECIMAL(10, 8), longitude DECIMAL(11, 8))

CREATE TABLE event_details (event_id INT, location_id INT, participants INT, duration_minutes INT, FOREIGN KEY (event_id) REFERENCES historical_events(event_id), FOREIGN KEY (location_id) REFERENCES locations(location_id))
CREATE TABLE user_events (user_id INT, event_id INT, attendance_status VARCHAR(50), FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id), FOREIGN KEY (event_id) REFERENCES historical_events(event_id))
